        <updateDate>2021-10-28T15:20:50Z</updateDate>
        <text>
          <![CDATA[ <p><b>Veterans 2nd Amendment Protection Act</b></p>  <p>This bill prohibits the Department of Veterans Affairs (VA) from transmitting certain information to the National Instant Criminal Background Check System (NICS) utilized by licensed importers or dealers of firearms. </p> <p>Specifically, the bill prohibits the VA from transmitting personally identifying information of a veteran or a beneficiary to the NICS solely on the basis that such veteran or beneficiary has an appointed fiduciary to manage their benefits, unless there is an order or finding of a judicial authority that such veteran or beneficiary is a danger to themselves or others.</p>]]>
        </text>
      </summary>
